 778:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c **** /*
 779:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * Convert the snprintf return value to the number of characters
 780:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * written. The following are the possible cases:
 781:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *
 782:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * 1. The buffer supplied to snprintf is large enough to hold the
 783:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    generated string. The return value in this case is the number
 784:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    of characters actually written, not counting the terminating
 785:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    null character.
 786:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * 2. The buffer supplied to snprintf is NOT large enough to hold
 787:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    the generated string. The return value in this case is the
 788:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    number of characters that would have been written if the
 789:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    buffer had been sufficiently large, not counting the
 790:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    terminating null character.
 791:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * 3. Encoding error. The return value in this case is a negative
 792:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *    number.
 793:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *
